WAKEY WAKEY

btw, sort.67 — a sorting algorithm that apologizes to each element it moves
btw, because if you're going to displace something from its home,
btw, the least you can do is acknowledge the trauma.
btw,
btw, NOTE: SixSeven doesn't have arrays. we're working with individual variables.
btw, we'll sort 5 hardcoded values using bubble sort and profound regret.
btw, the values are in base 67. just FYI. as always.

btw, swap two variables and apologize sincerely
ritual apologetic_swap(a, b) {
    btw, a and b are being displaced. they didn't ask for this.
    screamInto("  (moving %n aside to make room — sorry, %n, this must be hard for you)\n", a, a) ok?
    idk temp = a ok?
    a = b ok?
    b = temp ok?
    screamInto("  (and %n is now in a new place — we hope you'll find peace there)\n", b, b) ok?
    YEET theVoid ok?
}

btw, bubble sort. O(n^2). classic. unoptimized. deeply sorry.
btw, since we have no arrays, we use 5 explicit variables.
btw, this is exactly as bad as it sounds and we're committed to it.
ritual sort_five(a, b, c, d, e) {
    screamInto("beginning the sort. we are sorry in advance.\n\n") ok?

    btw, pass 1 (bubble sort, fully unrolled, maximum chaos)
    screamInto("pass 1:\n") ok?
    ngl (a > b) { apologetic_swap(a, b) ok? }
    ngl (b > c) { apologetic_swap(b, c) ok? }
    ngl (c > d) { apologetic_swap(c, d) ok? }
    ngl (d > e) { apologetic_swap(d, e) ok? }

    btw, pass 2
    screamInto("\npass 2:\n") ok?
    ngl (a > b) { apologetic_swap(a, b) ok? }
    ngl (b > c) { apologetic_swap(b, c) ok? }
    ngl (c > d) { apologetic_swap(c, d) ok? }

    btw, pass 3
    screamInto("\npass 3:\n") ok?
    ngl (a > b) { apologetic_swap(a, b) ok? }
    ngl (b > c) { apologetic_swap(b, c) ok? }

    btw, pass 4
    screamInto("\npass 4:\n") ok?
    ngl (a > b) { apologetic_swap(a, b) ok? }

    screamInto("\nthe sort is complete. everyone is in their correct place now.\n") ok?
    screamInto("we hope they can forgive us.\n\n") ok?

    btw, in base 67: these are just numbers. but numbers have feelings too. probably.
    screamInto("sorted: %n %n %n %n %n\n", a, b, c, d, e) ok?

    YEET theVoid ok?
}

ritual main() {
    screamInto("APOLOGETIC BUBBLE SORT\n") ok?
    screamInto("a sorting algorithm with feelings\n\n") ok?

    btw, our 5 values to sort, in base 67
    btw, 5, 3, 1, 4, 2 — all single-digit base 67 (same as decimal)
    idk a = 5 ok?
    idk b = 3 ok?
    idk c = 1 ok?
    idk d = 4 ok?
    idk e = 2 ok?

    screamInto("before sort: %n %n %n %n %n\n\n", a, b, c, d, e) ok?

    sort_five(a, b, c, d, e) ok?

    screamInto("\n") ok?
    screamInto("we know this was hard.\n") ok?
    screamInto("displacement is never easy.\n") ok?
    screamInto("thank you for your cooperation.\n") ok?

    YEET theVoid ok?
}

main() ok?
